event_description: https://developer-docs.netscaler.com/en-us/netscaler-syslog-message-reference/current-release
When a server side and a client side TCP connection is delinked.These are the connections which are being tracked by netscaler like HTTP
When a TCP connection terminates.The logged data indicates the number of bytes transmitted and received over the connection and lso the connection start and end time
When a server side and a client side TCP connection is delinked.These are the connections which are not being tracked by netscaler like FTP,telnet etc
When a server side and a client side TCP connection for RNAT are delinked we need to log the connection information
When a server side and a client side TCP connection for RNAT are delinked we need to log the connection information

Logs the TCP connection related information for a connection belonging to a SSLVPN session
An SSLVPN connection timed out.The information about the connection start and end time the amount of data transferred and received are present in the message date
When a UDP flow , within a SSLVPN session, terminates
A SSLVPN session receives a HTTP request
A non-http resource access is denied by policy engine. The denied policy name is captured in the log message.
A http resource access is denied by policy engine. The denied policy name is captured in the log message.
SSLVPN license limit reached
Logs with severity ERROR when client security check for a SSLVPN session fails, otherwise logs with severity DEBUG
Logs with severity ERROR when client security expression evaluates to False, otherwise logs with severity DEBUG
After a user logs into SSLVPN and the group for the user has been extracted
Gives debug information of session before removing session intentionally
